Winston Ko was appointed Deans Dean of the http://www.ls.ucdavis.edu/about/mps/ Division of Mathematical and Physical Sciences  in 2003 (see http://www.ls.ucdavis.edu/about/mps/messagefromdean.aspx message from the dean). He joined the University of California, Davis Physics Department of Physics faculty in 1972 according to his http://www.ls.ucdavis.edu/about/mps/deanbio.aspx/ curriculum vitae. His http://www.physics.ucdavis.edu/Text/Ko.html/ research has focused on experimental particle physics, which means trying to understand the fundamental structure of matter.


